59: /**
60:  * A nioSelector interface for doing non-blocking multi-connection network I/O.
61:  * <p>
62:  * This class works with {@link NetworkSend} and {@link NetworkReceive} to transmit size-delimited network requests and
63:  * responses.
64:  * <p>
65:  * A connection can be added to the nioSelector associated with an integer id by doing
66:  *
67:  * <pre>
68:  * nioSelector.connect(&quot;42&quot;, new InetSocketAddress(&quot;google.com&quot;, server.port), 64000, 64000);
69:  * </pre>
70:  *
71:  * The connect call does not block on the creation of the TCP connection, so the connect method only begins initiating
72:  * the connection. The successful invocation of this method does not mean a valid connection has been established.
73:  *
74:  * Sending requests, receiving responses, processing connection completions, and disconnections on the existing
75:  * connections are all done using the <code>poll()</code> call.
76:  *
77:  * <pre>
78:  * nioSelector.send(new NetworkSend(myDestination, myBytes));
79:  * nioSelector.send(new NetworkSend(myOtherDestination, myOtherBytes));
80:  * nioSelector.poll(TIMEOUT_MS);
81:  * </pre>
82:  *
83:  * The nioSelector maintains several lists that are reset by each call to <code>poll()</code> which are available via
84:  * various getters. These are reset by each call to <code>poll()</code>.
85:  *
86:  * This class is not thread safe!
87:  */
